TradingAgents (Claude Code Plugin)
Copyright 2026 namikos

This product is a derivative work of and includes design ideas, agent role
definitions, and workflow patterns adapted from:

    TradingAgents: Multi-Agents LLM Financial Trading Framework
    https://github.com/TauricResearch/TradingAgents
    Copyright TauricResearch and contributors
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

Specifically, the following parts of this plugin are inspired by or adapted
from the upstream project:

  - The agent role taxonomy (Fundamentals/Technical/News/Sentiment analyst,
    Bull/Bear researcher, Trader, Risk Manager).
  - The sequential workflow stages: parallel analyst research, bull/bear
    debate, trader synthesis, risk-manager approval.
  - The output convention `FINAL TRANSACTION PROPOSAL: **BUY/HOLD/SELL**`.
  - The system-prompt structure of each agent role (rewritten and adapted
    for Claude Code Agent Teams + MCP tools).

In addition, the v1.0 "Substanz Edition" extension also draws inspiration
from a second upstream project:

    AI Hedge Fund: Multi-Agent Investment Research with Famous-Investor Personas
    https://github.com/virattt/ai-hedge-fund
    Copyright virattt and contributors
    Licensed under the MIT License

Specifically, the following parts of this plugin are inspired by or adapted
from virattt/ai-hedge-fund:

  - The famous-investor persona pattern (Buffett, Graham, Munger, Burry,
    Wood, Ackman, Lynch, Fisher, Druckenmiller, Damodaran, Pabrai, Taleb,
    Jhunjhunwala) as parallel signal-producing agents.
  - The structured signal output schema (signal direction + confidence)
    as a programmatically-aggregable agent contract — adapted into the
    JSON Signal Footer convention used throughout this plugin.
  - The portfolio-manager-as-signal-aggregator pattern (here implemented
    as the trader's confidence-weighted aggregation step).

Each persona prompt was rewritten from scratch for Claude Code; no source
code from virattt/ai-hedge-fund is incorporated. The MIT terms of the
upstream are compatible with this plugin's Apache-2.0 license.

The native Claude Code orchestration (Agent Teams, mailbox messaging, plan
approval, MCP server, plugin packaging, the read-only Next.js dashboard,
and the quantitative MCP toolkit including DCF, Kelly, ATR, Sharpe, Sortino,
Max-Drawdown, factor exposure, options chain, short interest, and SEC EDGAR
integration) is original to this project.

